HEADWORD: Wifely
<hw>Wife"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>w⟦imac⟧flic</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Becoming or life; of or pertaining to a wife.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Wifely</xex> patience.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

